tid.helpText: The tracking ID is the unique identifier of your Google Analytics account. [Learn more](https://support.google.com/analytics/thread/13109681?hl=en)

exp.helpText: Run Google Optimize server-side experiments. It does precisely what ga("set", "exp", "$experimentId.$variationId") would do. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/optimize/devguides/experiments)

ea.helpText: This value of this field will be sent as Event Action to Google Analytics. [Learn more](https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/1033068?hl=en)

dp.helpText: The path portion of the page URL. Should begin with `/` [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/analytics/devguides/collection/protocol/v1/parameters#dp)

dl.helpText: Use this parameter to send the full URL of the page on which content resides. Defaults to current full URL. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/analytics/devguides/collection/protocol/v1/parameters#dl)

dh.helpText: Specifies the hostname from which content was hosted. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/analytics/devguides/collection/protocol/v1/parameters#dh)

ni.helpText: Non-interaction events are not taken into account when Google Analytics calculates bounces and session duration. [Learn more](https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/1033068?hl=en#NonInteractionEvents)

aip.helpText: This will anonymize the visitor IP address in your Google Analytics UI. [Learn more](https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/2763052?hl=en)

ec.helpText: This value of this field will be sent as Event Category to Google Analytics. [Learn more](https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/1033068?hl=en)

el.helpText: This value of this field will be sent as Event Label to Google Analytics. [Learn more](https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/1033068?hl=en)

ev.helpText: This value of this field will be sent as Event Value to Google Analytics. [Learn more](https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/1033068?hl=en)

uid.helpText: This is intended to be a known identifier for a user provided by the site owner/library user. It must not itself be PII (personally identifiable information). [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/analytics/devguides/collection/protocol/v1/parameters#uid)

t.helpText: The type of hit will determine how Google Analytics process it. [Learn more](https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/6086082?hl=en)
